        <h1>UBC Technical Career Fair 2007</h1>

        <h2>presented by UBC CS/IEEE/Engineering Physics/MIS</h2>
      </div><!-- End page header -->

      <div id="sidebar">
        <!-- Start sidebar content -->

        <div class="sideHeader"></div><!-- Sidebar header -->
        <!-- sidebar content you enter in the page inspector -->
      </div><!-- End sidebar content -->

      <div id="content">
        <!-- Start content -->
        In 1994, the <strong>UBC Computer Science Students'
        Society</strong> held its first Computer Careers Fair. In
        that year there were less than fifty students in the
        graduating class, and twelve companies attending this
        inaugural event. Many of the students were like us, trying
        to pursue a career in a field they enjoyed. The careers
        fair presented opportunities to students to meet with
        employers looking for well-trained and talented prospects.
        Over a decade later, and the emergence of the Internet is
        changing the way people and businesses communicate. The
        market for computer technologies has never been more
        exciting.
        <br />
        <br />
        This year, we've partnered up with the <strong>UBC
        Engineering/Physics</strong>, the <strong>UBC Institute
        of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE)</strong>, and <strong>
	UBC Sauder's MIS</strong> for
        the first time ever to bring together a
        total of thirty-two companies. To accommodate this number
        of firms, the fair will be taking place in the Student
        Union Building's Ballroom (2nd floor).
        <br />
        <br />
        Details about resume workshops, company descriptions and
        weekly news updates will be accessible by students on this
        website.
        <br />
        Ideas for the web site are still being considered. We will
        be adding information as it comes If you have any concerns
        or comments on how we can improve the site, feel free to
        let us know.
        <br />
        <br />
        To all the students participating, good luck and may the
        2007 UBC Career Fair help guide you to a long and
        successful career.
      </div><!-- End content -->

